<h2 class="option option--annuity">Get a guaranteed income (annuity)</h2>

<h3>Key facts</h3>

<ol class="ordered-list">
  <li>This is currently the only option which gives you a guaranteed income.</li>
  <li>You can shop around for an annuity – you don’t have to buy one from your pension provider.</li>
  <li>You can buy an annuity for a fixed term or for the rest of your life.</li>
  <li>You can take up to 25% of your pot tax free - if you do this, under current pension rules, you must buy an annuity with the remaining 75% within 6 months or use one of the other options.</li>
  <li>If you’re currently receiving a pension income it’s likely that you’ve already bought an annuity or are taking an income from a final salary or career average (defined benefit) pension.</li>
  <li>There are many different types of annuity and it’s important you get the right one for you.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h3>Next steps</h3>
<h4 class="pull icon icon--questions">Questions to ask your provider:</h4>

<ul class="list list--questions">
  <li>Does my pot have any special features like a guaranteed annuity rate? (see ‘Getting started’)</li>
  <li>Do I qualify for an enhanced or impaired annuity (you’ll need to tell your provider if you smoke or have a medical condition)?</li>
  <li>What types of annuity do you offer?</li>
</ul>

