<h2 class="option option--chunks">Take cash in chunks</h2>

<h3>Key facts</h3>

<ol class="ordered-list">
  <li>Instead of taking your whole pot in one go, you take smaller chunks over time - 25% of each chunk you take out is tax free and the rest is taxable.</li>
  <li>The chunks of cash you take get taxed along with any other income you have, eg from work, savings or investments.</li>
  <li>You can spread the chunks out over multiple tax years to reduce your income which could mean you pay less tax.</li>
  <li>If you have multiple pots, you can take chunks of cash from one and continue to pay into others.</li>
  <li>Providers may describe this option as ‘Uncrystallised Funds Pension Lump Sum’ (UFPLS).</li>
</ol>

<p class="emphasise">If your pot has already been invested into a flexi-access drawdown fund you won’t be able to take any more tax-free cash and cannot use this option.</p>

<hr>

<h3>Next steps</h3>
<h4 class="pull icon icon--questions">Questions to ask your provider:</h4>

<ul class="list list--questions">
  <li>Do you offer Uncrystallised Funds Pension Lump Sum?</li>
  <li>Will you charge me a fee if I move my pot to a provider that offers this option?</li>
  <li>Does my pot have any special features like a guaranteed annuity rate? (see ‘Getting started’)</li>
</ul>

